WEBVTT

00:01.305 --> 00:03.177
PREVIOUSLY ON "WHITE COLLAR"...

00:03.264 --> 00:04.961
Peter: VINCENT ADLER --

00:05.048 --> 00:07.485
HE'S LOOKING FOR A SUNKEN U-BOAT
OFF THE NEW YORK COAST.

00:07.572 --> 00:09.922
I JUST WANT TO SAY THAT
IF WE'RE GONNA CONTINUE
WORKING TOGETHER,

00:10.010 --> 00:12.273
THEN WE REALLY SHOULD NOT
IGNORE THE OTHER NIGHT.

00:12.360 --> 00:14.188
LOOK, IT WAS --HOT.

00:14.275 --> 00:16.233
THE CHRYSLER BUILDING.
PAINTING IT FOR YOUR GIRLFRIEND?

00:16.320 --> 00:17.626
IT CALMS THE NERVES.

00:19.193 --> 00:21.499
Neal: MY GOD.

00:21.586 --> 00:22.457
YOU FOUND IT.

00:26.330 --> 00:30.160
IT'S NAZI PLUNDER
FROM ALL OVER EUROPE.

00:30.247 --> 00:32.119
THIS HAS GOT TO BE WORTH
BILLIONS OF DOLLARS.

00:33.381 --> 00:34.599
GET DOWN!

00:40.257 --> 00:41.432
YOU DID THIS.

00:41.519 --> 00:42.738
PETER,
THOSE WERE MASTERPIECES.

00:42.825 --> 00:44.522
I WOULD NEVERBURN THEM.
YOU KNOW THAT.

00:44.609 --> 00:46.307
BUT YOU'D STEAL THEM.THEN PROVE IT.

00:58.971 --> 01:01.104
WE'VE GOT TO HURRY.

01:01.191 --> 01:03.019
WE'RE ALMOST LOADED.

01:03.106 --> 01:04.586
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

01:04.673 --> 01:06.153
IT'S THE FEDS.
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.

01:13.377 --> 01:15.814
[ ENGINES WHIRRING ]

01:15.901 --> 01:18.339
[ WAILING CONTINUES ]

01:27.435 --> 01:28.914
GET AROUND THE FRONT
OF THAT PLANE.

01:29.001 --> 01:30.916
TEAM ONE, FLANK LEFT.

01:31.003 --> 01:32.396
TEAM THREE, FLANK RIGHT.
BOX HIM IN!

01:32.483 --> 01:34.006
WE CANNOT LET CAFFREY
GET AIRBORNE!

01:35.356 --> 01:36.531
WE'RE NOT GONNA MAKE IT.

01:36.618 --> 01:38.750
WE DON'T HAVE
A CHOICE, MOZ.

01:41.797 --> 01:43.581
WE HAVETO MAKE IT.

01:48.978 --> 01:51.067
Jones: WHAT COLOR
ARE YOUR EYES?

01:51.154 --> 01:52.721
BLUE.

01:52.808 --> 01:54.810
ARE YOU
A CRIMINAL CONSULTANT

01:54.897 --> 01:56.768
FOR THE FEDERAL BUREAU
OF INVESTIGATION?

01:56.855 --> 01:58.205
YES.

01:58.292 --> 01:59.902
OKAY.

01:59.989 --> 02:02.383
FOR A BASELINE, I'M GONNA
NEED YOU TO TELL A LIE.

02:03.732 --> 02:05.386
I'VE NEVER TOLD A LIE.

02:07.170 --> 02:09.607
GREAT.
WE'VE GOT OUR BASELINE.

02:09.694 --> 02:10.826
ASK HIM
ABOUT THE WAREHOUSE.

02:10.913 --> 02:12.654
SHORTLY BEFORE HIS DEATH,

02:12.741 --> 02:15.222
YOU CONFRONTED VINCENT ADLER
OUTSIDE OF A WAREHOUSE.

02:15.309 --> 02:16.571
WHAT WAS IN THAT
WAREHOUSE?

02:16.658 --> 02:18.486
A U-BOAT -- GERMAN,

02:18.573 --> 02:21.141
RECENTLY DREDGED OFF THE COAST
OF NEW YORK STATE.

02:21.228 --> 02:22.707
AND INSIDE
OF THAT U-BOAT?

02:22.794 --> 02:24.753
A COLLECTION OF ART
PLUNDERED BY THE NAZIS.

02:24.840 --> 02:26.058
WHAT HAPPENED?

02:26.146 --> 02:28.322
THE WAREHOUSE
BURST INTO FLAMES.

02:28.409 --> 02:29.410
[ PETER CHUCKLES ]

02:32.630 --> 02:34.632
DID YOU STEAL THE ART?

02:34.719 --> 02:36.721
NO.

02:38.854 --> 02:40.638
DO YOU KNOW WHO DID?

02:42.466 --> 02:43.598
NO.

02:43.685 --> 02:45.426
[ SIGHS ]

02:45.513 --> 02:48.559
Jones: ACCORDING TO THE READOUT,
HE'S TELLING THE TRUTH.

02:48.646 --> 02:50.257
IT'S 2:00 IN THE MORNING,
PETER.

02:50.344 --> 02:51.823
YOU GONNA KEEP ME HERE
ALL NIGHT?

02:51.910 --> 02:54.043
UNTIL I'M SATISFIED.

02:54.130 --> 02:56.176
NEXT QUESTION.

02:59.831 --> 03:00.876
HEY.

03:00.963 --> 03:01.877
HI.

03:06.360 --> 03:07.535
YOU LOOK EXHAUSTED.

03:07.622 --> 03:08.797
EVERYTHING OKAY?

03:08.884 --> 03:10.538
OH, JUST -- LONG NIGHT.

03:10.625 --> 03:13.062
SARA,
PETER MAY COME TO YOU

03:13.149 --> 03:15.151
AND ASK SOME QUESTIONS.ABOUT WHAT?

03:15.238 --> 03:16.761
HE THINKS
THE ART DIDN'T BURN.

03:16.848 --> 03:18.154
HOW'S THAT POSSIBLE?

03:19.547 --> 03:20.765
OH, HE THINKS
YOUTOOK IT.

03:20.852 --> 03:22.550
I WAS OFF-ANKLET
WHEN IT COULDHAVE HAPPENED.

03:22.637 --> 03:24.856
SO YOU NEED AN ALIBI.

03:24.943 --> 03:26.380
WHAT IS IT YOU'RE HOPING
I TELL HIM?

03:26.467 --> 03:27.772
THE TRUTH.

03:27.859 --> 03:29.209
ABOUT THE OTHER NIGHT.

03:29.296 --> 03:31.472
YOU WANT ME TO TELL HIM
EVERYTHING?

03:31.559 --> 03:34.039
'CAUSE THAT COULD GET
REALLY VERY AWKWARD.

03:38.087 --> 03:39.480
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:39.567 --> 03:41.308
SKIP THE GOOD PARTS.YEAH.

03:43.005 --> 03:44.876
DID YOU TAKE IT?
NO.

03:44.963 --> 03:46.965
DO YOU BELIEVE ME?

03:47.052 --> 03:48.706
YOU'RE A DAMN GOOD
CON MAN.

03:52.232 --> 03:54.234
CAFFREY...

03:54.321 --> 03:57.106
IF THAT ART ISOUT THERE...

03:57.193 --> 03:58.499
ANY IDEA WHO HAS IT?

04:29.007 --> 04:30.748
HER NAME IS LOLANA.

04:30.835 --> 04:33.055
SHE FROM ANY ISLAND
IN PARTICULAR?

04:33.142 --> 04:35.579
WHICHEVER ONE
YOUR HEART DESIRES.

04:39.279 --> 04:42.238
SO, I GUESS
THIS WAS FROM YOU?

04:43.935 --> 04:44.980
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

04:45.067 --> 04:46.155
HOW?

04:46.242 --> 04:48.026
IT WASN'T EASY.

04:48.113 --> 04:49.289
THE WAREHOUSE?

04:49.376 --> 04:50.638
I WORKED BACKWARDS

04:50.725 --> 04:52.117
FROM THE TRANSMITTER
YOU WIRED INTO THE LIMO.

04:52.204 --> 04:53.728
SECURITY?

04:53.815 --> 04:56.078
I GOT AROUND IT WITH
A LOCALIZED E.M. BURST.

04:56.165 --> 04:57.384
AND THE ART?

04:57.471 --> 04:58.733
ADLER HAD IT LOADED
ONTO A TRUCK.

04:58.820 --> 04:59.995
THE SWAP WASN'T HARD.

05:00.082 --> 05:02.084
AND THE TNT
WE GOT OFF THE SUB

05:02.171 --> 05:03.912
WAS UNSTABLE
AND EASY TO DETONATE.

05:03.999 --> 05:05.435
A PERFECT COVER.

05:08.612 --> 05:09.918
YOU DIDN'T TELL ME.

05:10.005 --> 05:12.921
PLAUSIBLE DENIABILITY
AND ALL.

05:14.749 --> 05:16.577
WE FINALLY GOT
OUR WHITE WHALE.

05:19.231 --> 05:21.277
[ SIGHS ]

05:23.323 --> 05:25.847
LOLANA, HUH?

05:25.934 --> 05:28.240
IN HAWAIIAN,
HER NAME MEANS "TO SOAR"...

05:28.328 --> 05:30.852
WHICH IS EXACTLY WHAT WE'RE
GONNA DO IN A VERY SHORT TIME.

05:30.939 --> 05:32.810
WELL, IT'S NOT THAT EASY.

05:32.897 --> 05:35.073
I JUST SPENT FIVE HOURS
IN INTERROGATION WITH PETER.

05:35.160 --> 05:36.684
HE SUSPECTS SOMETHING.

05:36.771 --> 05:38.947
ALL THE MORE REASON
FOR HASTE.

05:39.034 --> 05:40.296
HOW LONG
TO GET THINGS READY?

05:40.383 --> 05:41.602
JUST A FEW DAYS.

05:43.865 --> 05:45.040
I CAN LULL PETER.

05:45.127 --> 05:46.955
BUT WE DON'T RUSH THIS.

05:47.042 --> 05:49.436
WE TAKE OUR TIME.
WE DO IT RIGHT.

05:51.394 --> 05:54.702
TO OUR BEST
AND FINALSCORE.

05:59.141 --> 06:00.577
[ CLINK ]

06:20.467 --> 06:22.164
I PASSED
YOUR LIE DETECTOR.

06:22.251 --> 06:23.818
I'VE SEEN YOU
DO THAT BEFORE.

06:23.905 --> 06:25.341
ARE YOU SAYING
I CHEATED?

06:25.428 --> 06:26.560
I'VE SEEN YOU
DO THATBEFORE.

06:26.647 --> 06:28.300
ALL RIGHT, IF YOU'RE
NOT GONNA TALK TO ME,

06:28.388 --> 06:29.867
LET'S AT LEAST JUST
KEEP IT CIVIL, OKAY?

06:29.954 --> 06:33.218
FINE.
HOW 'BOUT THEM METS?

06:33.305 --> 06:35.438
WHAT'S WRONG? HMM?

06:35.525 --> 06:37.614
WHAT HAPPENED THAT
TURNED YOU AGAINST ME?

06:37.701 --> 06:39.094
ITURNED AGAINST YOU?

06:39.181 --> 06:40.661
PETER, WE'RE A TEAM.

06:40.748 --> 06:42.706
OHH.

06:42.793 --> 06:43.751
WE DID THIS.

06:46.536 --> 06:48.016
THIS IS OUR JOB.

06:48.103 --> 06:51.062
LET'S NOT MAKE A BIG DEAL
OUT OF IT.

07:08.863 --> 07:10.734
HMM.

07:12.344 --> 07:13.345
YOU'RE SMILING.

07:13.433 --> 07:15.130
I AM.

07:15.217 --> 07:17.567
TELL ME ABOUT GARY RYDELL.

07:20.222 --> 07:21.397
THAT'S YOU.

07:21.484 --> 07:23.007
YEAH, IT IS.

07:24.139 --> 07:25.706
REGALE ME.

07:25.793 --> 07:27.447
OH, IT WAS AN ALIAS
I USED YEARS AGO.

07:27.534 --> 07:29.013
RYDELL WAS A BIT
OF A PLAYBOY

07:29.100 --> 07:31.146
WITH AN UNCANNY ABILITY
TO WRECK EXPENSIVE CARS.

07:31.233 --> 07:33.496
OF COURSE.
ANYTHING ELSE?

07:33.583 --> 07:35.498
HE WAS
A WORLD-CLASS FENCER.

07:35.585 --> 07:36.717
AND?

07:38.240 --> 07:39.546
NEAL, I'VE READ THE FILE.

07:39.633 --> 07:41.025
AND A SMUGGLER.

07:41.112 --> 07:43.245
A WORLD-CLASS SMUGGLER.YEAH, I GET IT.

07:43.332 --> 07:45.247
YOU THINK I MIGHT ACTIVATE
MY RYDELL ALIAS

07:45.334 --> 07:46.770
IN ORDER TO SNEAK SOMETHING
OUT OF THE COUNTRY,

07:46.857 --> 07:48.555
SOMETHING LIKE
A STOLEN NAZI TREASURE?

07:48.642 --> 07:49.991
CROSSED MY MIND.

07:50.078 --> 07:52.515
I THINK THIS GUY
IS LOOKING FOR RYDELL.

07:52.602 --> 07:53.951
I WANT TO KNOW WHY.

07:54.038 --> 07:55.997
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:56.084 --> 07:57.302
DAVID LAWRENCE.

07:57.389 --> 07:58.478
YOU KNOW HIM.

07:58.565 --> 08:00.392
YEAH.
WE MET A FEW YEARS AGO.

08:00.480 --> 08:02.612
HE WAS SELLING PRE-COLUMBIAN
ART, AND I WAS --
BUYING.

08:02.699 --> 08:04.614
YEAH, BUYING.

08:04.701 --> 08:06.311
LAWRENCE WAS ALSO SUSPECTED

08:06.398 --> 08:09.358
OF ROBBING $60 MILLION
FROM THE FEDERAL RESERVE.

08:09.445 --> 08:11.012
HE FLED THE COUNTRY
ON A COMMERCIAL JET

08:11.099 --> 08:13.144
BEFORE WE COULD MAKE
THE ARREST.

08:13.231 --> 08:15.190
WE THINK HE LEFT
THE $60 MIL BEHIND.

08:15.277 --> 08:16.713
WELL, A SAFE ASSUMPTION.

08:16.800 --> 08:19.150
I MEAN, THE BAGGAGE FEES ALONE
WOULD'VE COST A FORTUNE.

08:19.237 --> 08:21.239
TWO DAYS AGO,

08:21.326 --> 08:23.677
WE TRACED AN E-MAIL HE SENT
TO A SERVER HERE IN NEW YORK.

08:23.764 --> 08:25.374
LAWRENCE WANTS YOU

08:25.461 --> 08:27.637
TO HELP HIM SMUGGLE THE CASH
OUT OF THE COUNTRY.

08:27.724 --> 08:29.073
YOU WANT ME TO STRIKE UP
A DEAL WITH HIM

08:29.160 --> 08:30.379
AND LEAD YOU
TO THE $60 MILLION.

08:30.466 --> 08:33.600
WE'LL LET YOU KNOW
WHEN WE MAKE CONTACT.

08:36.516 --> 08:38.735
YOU REALLY THINK
HE'S GONNA TAKE THIS RISK?

08:38.822 --> 08:41.521
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

08:41.608 --> 08:43.784
IF YOU WERE ONE STEP AWAY

08:43.871 --> 08:47.222
FROM PULLING OFF THE BIGGEST
SCORE IN YOUR LIFE...

08:47.309 --> 08:49.137
COULD YOU LET IT GO?

08:49.224 --> 08:51.356
Neal: PETER'S NOT PLAYING
A HUNCH.

08:51.443 --> 08:53.141
HE KNOWS SOMETHING.IMPOSSIBLE.

08:53.228 --> 08:54.708
HE'S BREATHING
DOWN MY NECK.

08:54.795 --> 08:56.840
HE'S MESSING WITH YOUR HEAD.
THAT'S WHAT SUITS DO.

08:56.927 --> 08:58.363
SO, THERE'S NOTHING
FROM THE HEIST

08:58.450 --> 08:59.669
THAT COULD BE TIED
BACK TO ME?

09:01.889 --> 09:03.412
MOZ.

09:03.499 --> 09:04.979
YOU KNOW THAT ART STUDIO

09:05.066 --> 09:06.502
WHERE YOU KEEP ALL
THE PAINTINGS YOU'VE DONE?

09:06.589 --> 09:07.459
WHAT ABOUT IT?

09:07.547 --> 09:09.157
NOW IT'S JUST A STUDIO.

09:10.854 --> 09:13.553
YOU SWITCHED MY ART
FOR THE ART ON THE SUB?

09:13.640 --> 09:16.251
NEAL, YOU'RE TALENTED,
BUT VAN DYCK HAS YOU BEAT.

09:16.338 --> 09:17.731
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.

09:17.818 --> 09:20.560
LOOK, THEY RAN FORENSICS TESTS
ON THE BURNED WAREHOUSE.

09:20.647 --> 09:22.910
THEY NEEDED TO FIND TRACES
OF PAINT AND CANVAS.

09:22.997 --> 09:24.520
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT THIS MEANS?

09:24.607 --> 09:26.914
NOTHING COULD SURVIVE
THAT FIRE.

09:28.785 --> 09:30.352
NOTHING SHOULDHAVE
SURVIVED THE FIRE.

09:30.439 --> 09:32.354
THANK YOU.

09:37.098 --> 09:38.752
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACH ]

09:38.839 --> 09:41.450
[ ELIZABETH SIGHS ]

09:41.537 --> 09:43.104
HONEY, YOU'VE BEEN STARING
AT THAT ALL NIGHT.

09:43.191 --> 09:44.453
HE TOOK IT, EL.

09:44.540 --> 09:46.890
I KNOW HE TOOK THE ART.

09:46.977 --> 09:48.457
I'M STANDING THERE,

09:48.544 --> 09:50.372
WATCHING THE WAREHOUSE
GO UP IN FLAMES,

09:50.459 --> 09:53.462
AND THIS FLOATS
DOWN AT MY FEET.

09:53.549 --> 09:55.377
IT'S A PIECE
OF THE SAME PAINTING

09:55.464 --> 09:58.119
THAT WAS IN HIS APARTMENT.

09:58.206 --> 09:59.642
YOU'RE POSITIVE
IT'S THE SAME?

09:59.729 --> 10:01.078
HOW MANY PAINTINGS LIKE THIS

10:01.165 --> 10:03.472
COULD THERE BE
OF THE CHRYSLER BUILDING?

10:03.559 --> 10:05.866
ACTUALLY, YOU'D BE SURPRISED.
ART DECO STARTED IN PARIS,

10:05.953 --> 10:08.912
SO THERE WAS A LOT OF EUROPEAN
INTEREST IN THE CHRYSLER.

10:08.999 --> 10:10.218
YEAH, HERE.

10:10.305 --> 10:13.525
IT'S BEEN AROUND,
WHAT, 80 YEARS?

10:13.613 --> 10:15.876
HERE IT IS.

10:15.963 --> 10:18.879
"COUNTLESS ARTISTS WOULD
INTERPRET THE CHRYSLER'S MAJESTY

10:18.966 --> 10:21.359
USING A VARIETY
OF STYLES AND TECHNIQUES."

10:21.446 --> 10:23.753
IT WAS BUILT IN 1931.

10:23.840 --> 10:25.146
COULD'VE BEEN ON THE SUB.

10:25.233 --> 10:26.843
OR MAYBE NEAL PAINTED IT.

10:26.930 --> 10:28.715
OR MAYBE YOU'VE BEEN
CHASING HIM FOR SO LONG,

10:28.802 --> 10:30.064
YOU DON'T KNOW HOW TO STOP.

10:30.151 --> 10:32.109
OR MAYBE I KNOW HIM BETTER
THAN ANYONE ELSE.

10:34.111 --> 10:36.810
[ SIGHS ]

10:36.897 --> 10:41.031
IF NOT HIM, THEN MOZZIE
OR ALEX.

10:41.118 --> 10:43.947
NEAL'S INVOLVED...
SOMEHOW.

10:44.034 --> 10:45.514
WELL, THERE'S A WAY
YOU CAN FIND OUT.

10:45.601 --> 10:47.037
HAVE THE FORENSICS TEAM
TEST IT.

10:47.124 --> 10:49.039
IF IT'S FROM THE 1930s,
THEN YOU KNOW IT'S NOT HIS.

10:49.126 --> 10:51.259
I CAN'T INVOLVE THE BUREAU,
NOT YET.

10:51.346 --> 10:52.826
IF I'M RIGHT...

10:52.913 --> 10:54.741
AND NEAL'S BEHIND THIS...

10:54.828 --> 10:57.047
HE GOES DOWN.

10:57.134 --> 10:58.658
AND SO DO I.

11:01.617 --> 11:03.358
I COULD HAVE IT TESTED.

11:03.445 --> 11:05.534
YOU HAVE A LAB IN THE BASEMENT
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT?

11:05.621 --> 11:07.536
NO, THE DeARMITT GALLERY.

11:07.623 --> 11:10.104
THEY GO THROUGH PRIVATE LABS
TO AUTHENTICATE WORK.

11:10.191 --> 11:11.627
IT'S BEEN YEARS
SINCE YOU WORKED THERE.

11:11.714 --> 11:13.411
I KEEP IN TOUCH.

11:13.498 --> 11:14.804
YOU COULD CALL IN A FAVOR?

11:14.891 --> 11:17.024
FOR YOU?

11:17.111 --> 11:18.895
ANYTHING.

11:28.383 --> 11:29.558
WE MADE CONTACT
WITH LAWRENCE

11:29.645 --> 11:31.125
THROUGH YOUR RYDELL
E-MAIL ACCOUNT.

11:31.212 --> 11:32.996
Peter: HE WANTS TO MEET YOU AT
THE GRAMERCY FENCING CLUB

11:33.083 --> 11:34.476
IN A FEW HOURS.

11:34.563 --> 11:36.957
WHY CAN'T GUYS LIKE YOU
EVER JUST GRAB A BEER?

11:37.044 --> 11:39.220
IMPORTED OR DOMESTIC?

11:39.307 --> 11:42.179
JUST MEET WITH HIM,
LEAD US BACK TO THE CASH.

11:42.266 --> 11:43.615
I'M PULLING
YOUR ANKLET.

11:43.703 --> 11:45.313
AS USUAL.

11:45.400 --> 11:47.054
DON'T GET COCKY.
WE'LL BE LISTENING.

11:47.141 --> 11:48.620
AND I'LL BE CLOSE.

11:49.796 --> 11:52.407
THANK YOU.

11:52.494 --> 11:54.278
[ FOILS CLANKING ]

12:06.464 --> 12:07.770
DAVID.

12:07.857 --> 12:09.076
GOOD TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

12:09.163 --> 12:11.252
IT IS GOOD
TO BE SEEN, GARY.

12:11.339 --> 12:12.775
YOU KNOW,
I MISSED THIS PLACE.

12:12.862 --> 12:14.908
BEAUTY HERE --

12:14.995 --> 12:16.779
THEY ENCOURAGE DISGUISES.

12:16.866 --> 12:18.172
WHO ARE YOU HIDING FROM?

12:19.651 --> 12:22.002
YOU NEVER
CAN BE TOO CAREFUL.

12:25.788 --> 12:28.269
IS THAT WHY I HAVEN'T SEEN YOU
IN THE LAST SIX YEARS?

12:28.356 --> 12:30.314
OH, I RETIRED
TO THE ISLANDS.

12:30.401 --> 12:32.447
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:32.534 --> 12:34.971
MY FRIEND,
IF YOU'RE RETIRED...

12:35.058 --> 12:37.974
THEN WHY AREN'T WE
PLAYING SHUFFLEBOARD?

12:38.061 --> 12:40.585
I HAVEN'T HEARD OF YOU IN THE
LAST SIX YEARS, EITHER, GARY.

12:40.672 --> 12:43.153
HOW DO I KNOW YOU'RE STILL
ON YOUR GAME?

12:43.240 --> 12:45.155
MAYBE I'M THAT GOOD.

12:45.242 --> 12:46.983
OR MAYBE
YOU LOST A STEP.

12:55.905 --> 12:57.907
THAT WAS MY TIE.

12:57.994 --> 13:00.214
COME ON. SHOW ME
YOU'RE STILL AS GOOD

13:00.301 --> 13:01.911
AS THE GARY RYDELL
I USED TO KNOW.

13:03.391 --> 13:06.394
WELL, I'M STILL USING
A FRENCH GRIP...

13:08.091 --> 13:10.615
...STILL A FAN
OF THE DEPASSEMENT ATTAQUE.

13:16.665 --> 13:18.536
LET'S GET TO THE POINT --
YOU STOLE $60 MILLION

13:18.623 --> 13:20.277
BUT COULDN'T GET IT
OUT OF THE COUNTRY.

13:20.364 --> 13:21.757
NOW YOU NEED ME
TO MOVE IT FOR YOU.

13:21.844 --> 13:22.802
TELL ME I'M WRONG.

13:26.893 --> 13:28.372
NICE ATTAQUE COMPOSéE.

13:28.459 --> 13:30.244
FEINT LEFT, THRUST RIGHT --
MY SIGNATURE.

13:30.331 --> 13:31.375
I REMEMBER.

13:32.986 --> 13:34.770
GET ME AND THE GREEN
OUT OF THE COUNTRY,

13:34.857 --> 13:36.511
AND YOU WILL EARN 10%.

13:36.598 --> 13:39.079
20%.

13:39.166 --> 13:42.343
WELL, I'M IN NO POSITION
TO ARGUE.

13:42.430 --> 13:43.779
WHERE'S THE CASH?

13:43.866 --> 13:45.781
CLOSE.

13:47.043 --> 13:49.916
SET IT UP.
I'LL BE IN TOUCH.

14:01.318 --> 14:02.885
IT IS CRUEL
AND UNUSUAL PUNISHMENT

14:02.972 --> 14:04.713
FOR YOU TO BRING ME
BACK HERE LIKE THIS.

14:04.800 --> 14:07.281
YES, BUT I'M
FINALLY SMILING.

14:07.368 --> 14:09.457
WHAT'S YOUR PLAN FOR MOVING
LAWRENCE'S MONEY?

14:09.544 --> 14:10.675
I'LL TAKE IT OUT BY BOAT.

14:10.762 --> 14:11.981
WHY A BOAT?

14:12.068 --> 14:14.418
ONE, WE'RE TALKING
ABOUT A LARGE SHIPMENT

14:14.505 --> 14:17.552
THAT'S EASIER TO MOVE
ON THE WATER THAN BY AIR.

14:17.639 --> 14:19.989
AND, TWO, IT'S EASIER
TO PAY OFF DOCK WORKERS

14:20.076 --> 14:21.817
THAN TSA EMPLOYEES.[ SIGHS ] SOLD.

14:21.904 --> 14:24.298
DIANA, I WANT A TEAM
AT THE HARBOR.YOU GOT IT.

14:24.385 --> 14:26.648
BLUE.

14:33.176 --> 14:34.830
MM.

14:34.917 --> 14:36.527
I'VE DRIVEN YOU
TO DUMPSTER DIVE?

14:36.614 --> 14:39.052
A SOUVENIR OF NEAL CAFFREY'S
IMPERFECT MOMENT?

14:39.139 --> 14:40.662
PRICELESS.

14:47.625 --> 14:49.584
Neal: YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE!Cindy: GRANDMA INSISTED.

14:49.671 --> 14:51.716
OH, YOU'RE BOTH
SO THOUGHTFUL!

14:51.803 --> 14:53.762
MOZZIE, YOU, OF COURSE,

14:53.849 --> 14:55.764
KNOW JUNE'S
BEAUTIFUL GRANDDAUGHTER.

14:55.851 --> 14:57.374
OH. HI, CINDY.

14:57.461 --> 14:58.985
GRANDMA SAID
THE TWO OF YOU

14:59.072 --> 15:00.900
HAVE BEEN, UH, UP TO SOMETHING
IN HERE.

15:00.987 --> 15:03.772
OH, YOU KNOW,
IDLE HANDS AND ALL.

15:03.859 --> 15:05.208
AND THEY BROUGHT US
COFFEE!

15:05.295 --> 15:06.949
OH, AND COOKIES!

15:07.036 --> 15:08.429
I'LL BE BACK
FOR THE TRAY.

15:08.516 --> 15:10.910
NO. NO, NO.
DON'T TROUBLE YOURSELF.

15:10.997 --> 15:12.520
Mozzie: YEAH.
WE'LL BRING IT DOWN.

15:12.607 --> 15:14.087
EVERYTHING
LOOKS BEAUTIFUL.

15:14.174 --> 15:16.393
YEAH. HEY, UM...

15:16.480 --> 15:18.482
THANKS AGAIN
FOR EVERYTHING.

15:18.569 --> 15:19.875
THANKS. YEAH.
THANK YOU.

15:22.051 --> 15:23.313
LOVELY GIRL.

15:23.400 --> 15:24.749
I'M GONNA MISS
THIS PLACE.

15:24.836 --> 15:27.752
YEAH, AND THE VIEWS.
YEAH.

15:27.839 --> 15:31.756
ALL RIGHT. PETER'S TEAM
IS SETTING UP A HARBOR STING.

15:31.843 --> 15:33.454
OH, WELL, PERFECT.

15:33.541 --> 15:36.848
SO WHILE THE FBI IS BUSY
COLLARING LAWRENCE BY SEA,

15:36.936 --> 15:39.242
WE'LL BE MAKING OUR ESCAPE
PAR AVION...

15:39.329 --> 15:40.722
BY AIR.
HMM.

15:40.809 --> 15:43.246
I HAVE PROCURED
OUR GETAWAY VEHICLE.

15:45.466 --> 15:48.164
VOILà. BEHOLD --

15:48.251 --> 15:49.644
THE 400 SERIES
TWIN OTTER.

15:49.731 --> 15:50.993
IS IT BIG ENOUGH?

15:51.080 --> 15:52.516
THINK OF IT
AS A KARDASHIAN --

15:52.603 --> 15:53.996
WHAT IT LACKS IN REFINEMENT,

15:54.083 --> 15:58.000
IT MAKES UP FOR
IN CARGO SPACE.

15:58.087 --> 16:00.089
YOU'RE NOT SOLD.NO, THE PLANE'S GREAT.

16:00.176 --> 16:02.091
I'M JUST --
I'M WORRIED ABOUT PETER.

16:02.178 --> 16:03.527
HE'S HOLDING
SOMETHING, MOZ.

16:03.614 --> 16:05.399
IF HE'S GOT A CARD
HE HASN'T PLAYED YET,

16:05.486 --> 16:07.444
WE'RE NOT GONNA GET FAR.

16:07.531 --> 16:11.666
OKAY. SO, WHAT'S THE BEST WAY
TO FIND OUT WHAT PETER KNOWS?

16:11.753 --> 16:13.668
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

16:15.017 --> 16:16.062
HEY, NEAL.

16:16.149 --> 16:17.193
HEY.

16:17.280 --> 16:18.716
PETER'S NOT HERE.I KNOW.

16:18.803 --> 16:20.240
I WANT TO SEE YOU.

16:22.546 --> 16:24.766
I WAS HOPING
WE COULD TALK.

16:28.248 --> 16:30.598
COME ON IN.
THANK YOU.

16:32.208 --> 16:34.906
YOU, UM...
WANT SOME COFFEE?

16:34.994 --> 16:36.647
I NEVER SAY NO
TO GOOD COFFEE.

16:36.734 --> 16:38.693
HUH. OKAY.

16:38.780 --> 16:40.956
WELL, THEN,
WHY DON'T I POUR,

16:41.043 --> 16:43.828
AND YOU TELL ME
WHY YOU DROPPED BY

16:43.915 --> 16:45.569
KNOWING MY HUSBAND'S
NOT HERE?
HMM.

16:45.656 --> 16:48.181
I DON'T KNOW.

16:48.268 --> 16:50.096
HE SUDDENLY
DOESN'T TRUST ME.

16:50.183 --> 16:52.054
I DON'T KNOW
HOW SUDDEN IT IS.

16:52.141 --> 16:54.100
I DON'T KNOW --
BREAKING OUT OF PRISON,

16:54.187 --> 16:55.927
STEALING THE MUSIC BOX,
ALMOST SHOOTING FOWLER.

16:56.015 --> 16:57.451
YOU WANT ME TO GO ON?

16:57.538 --> 17:00.280
NOT PARTICULARLY, NO.

17:00.367 --> 17:01.890
LOOK, HE WANTS TO TRUST YOU,

17:01.977 --> 17:04.023
BUT YOU HAVE THIS --
I DON'T KNOW -- HABIT

17:04.110 --> 17:06.634
OF DOING THE WRONG THING
FOR THE RIGHT REASONS.

17:06.721 --> 17:10.029
YOU'RE SAYING I'M IMPULSIVE
BUT I HAVE A GOOD HEART?

17:10.116 --> 17:11.856
MAYBE YOU CAN TRY
AND BALANCE THE TWO?

17:13.162 --> 17:15.251
YOU MAKE A FAIR POINT.

17:15.338 --> 17:16.861
AND A GREAT CUP OF COFFEE.

17:16.948 --> 17:18.950
BUT I LIKE A LITTLE BIT
OF MILK IN MINE.

17:19.038 --> 17:20.996
YES.
OKAY.

17:23.825 --> 17:25.653
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

17:28.786 --> 17:30.614
TELL ME WHEN.

17:30.701 --> 17:32.399
WHEN.

17:32.486 --> 17:34.227
[ SETS DOWN CUP ]

17:34.314 --> 17:37.056
TO THE RIGHT THINGS...

17:37.143 --> 17:39.319
FOR THE RIGHT REASONS.

17:47.066 --> 17:50.330
PICKED UP A COPY
ON THE WAY HOME.

17:50.417 --> 17:52.114
Mozzie:
AND YOU'RE SURE MRS. SUIT

17:52.201 --> 17:54.508
WAS INTENTIONALLY
HIDING IT FROM YOU?
YES.

17:54.595 --> 17:56.727
YOU KNOW, I GUESS A PART OF ME
ALWAYS KNEW

17:56.814 --> 17:58.773
WHEN PUSH COMES TO SHOVE,
SHE'D CHOOSE PETER.

17:58.860 --> 18:00.514
WELL, HE'S HER HUSBAND.

18:00.601 --> 18:02.472
YEAH, HAVE THEY EVER SWAPPED
OSSOBUCO RECIPES?

18:02.559 --> 18:03.865
WHICH APPARENTLY
MEANS NOTHING.

18:05.823 --> 18:07.782
WAIT A MINUTE.

18:07.869 --> 18:09.175
THIS HAS TO BE IT.

18:09.262 --> 18:10.437
THE CHRYSLER BUILDING?

18:10.524 --> 18:12.569
YEAH, PETER WAS HERE
THE NIGHT BEFORE THE FIRE.

18:12.656 --> 18:14.745
THIS PAINTING WAS ON THAT EASEL.
HE COMMENTED ON IT.

18:14.832 --> 18:17.008
YOU REMEMBER?

18:19.010 --> 18:20.969
DID YOU PUT IT
ON THE SUB?

18:21.056 --> 18:22.623
YOU KNOW, IN ALL HONESTY,

18:22.710 --> 18:24.886
I-IT WASN'T ONE
OF YOUR BETTER WORKS.

18:24.973 --> 18:26.670
WHAT IF IT DIDN'T BURN,
MOZ?

18:26.757 --> 18:28.542
IF HE HAD IT,
YOU'D BE IN CUFFS ALREADY.

18:28.629 --> 18:30.761
NO. I KNOW HIM.
HE'D WANT TO BE SURE.

18:30.848 --> 18:34.156
SO HE GAVE IT TO THE FEDS
TO RUN SOME TESTS

18:34.243 --> 18:36.245
TO SEE IF THE PAINTING
PREDATED THE SUB

18:36.332 --> 18:37.725
AS OPPOSED
TO, SAY, LAST WEEK.

18:37.812 --> 18:39.988
IF THE BUREAU RAN THE TESTS,
HE'D HAVE THE RESULTS BY NOW.

18:40.075 --> 18:41.729
HE DOESN'T WANT
THE FBI INVOLVED.

18:41.816 --> 18:43.383
HE DOESN'T WANT IT
ON THE RECORD.

18:43.470 --> 18:44.558
WHY NOT?

18:44.645 --> 18:46.342
TO PROTECT ME.

18:46.429 --> 18:48.866
OR TO PROTECT HIMSELF.

18:48.953 --> 18:50.607
MAYBE.

18:50.694 --> 18:53.349
SO, IF HE DIDN'T GIVE IT
TO THE FBI LAB,

18:53.436 --> 18:54.394
WHO ELSE COULD TEST IT?

18:56.135 --> 18:57.832
ELIZABETH?ELIZABETH?

18:57.919 --> 18:59.529
YEAH, SHE COMES
FROM AN ART BACKGROUND,

18:59.616 --> 19:01.009
AND SHE KNOWS
ABOUT THE PAINTING.

19:01.096 --> 19:03.142
I SHOULD KEEP
AN EYE ON HER.

19:04.491 --> 19:06.014
IT'S WORTH A SHOT,
HAVERSHAM.

19:06.101 --> 19:08.234
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:08.321 --> 19:10.497
[ SEABIRDS CRYING,
AIR HORN BLOWS ]

19:12.586 --> 19:14.849
BEAUTIFUL DAY, GARY.

19:14.936 --> 19:18.200
YES, IT IS.

19:18.287 --> 19:21.421
I WAS WONDERING
IF YOU'D SHOW.

19:21.508 --> 19:24.032
I DIDN'T COME THIS FAR
TO BACK OUT NOW.

19:24.119 --> 19:25.773
I WASN'T RULING IT OUT.

19:25.860 --> 19:28.689
EVERY DAY THAT MONEY SITS THERE,
JUST OUT OF REACH.

19:28.776 --> 19:32.127
COMES A POINT WHERE YOU FINISH
THE JOB OR IT FINISHES YOU.

19:32.214 --> 19:34.564
YOU GET CAUGHT,
YOU LOSE EVERYTHING.

19:34.651 --> 19:36.958
ALREADY LOST EVERYTHING.

19:37.045 --> 19:39.482
WHEN I RAN, I RAN FAST.
DIDN'T LOOK BACK.

19:39.569 --> 19:41.267
SO...

19:41.354 --> 19:42.746
HOW'S THIS GONNA WORK?

19:42.833 --> 19:45.009
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:45.096 --> 19:46.881
ON YOUR GO,
THE INGENIEUR MINARD

19:46.968 --> 19:48.796
WILL PROVIDE YOU
AND YOUR CARGO

19:48.883 --> 19:52.103
SAFE AND DISCRETE PASSAGE
TO THE ISLAND OF SANTO ANTAO.

19:52.191 --> 19:54.105
ALL THE DOCUMENTATION
YOU MAY NEED UPON ARRIVAL

19:54.193 --> 19:57.761
IS IN THAT ENVELOPE --
I.D., PASSPORT, EVERYTHING.

19:57.848 --> 20:00.764
GETTING IN ISN'T MY CONCERN.
IT'S GETTING OUT.

20:00.851 --> 20:02.462
FOUR STEPS.

20:02.549 --> 20:04.855
STEP ONE, WE MOVE YOUR MONEY
HERE BY TRUCK.

20:04.942 --> 20:06.770
STEP TWO, MY INSIDE MAN
AT THE GATE,

20:06.857 --> 20:09.077
MR. RYAN IN CUSTOMS,

20:09.164 --> 20:10.600
LOOKS THE OTHER WAY

20:10.687 --> 20:13.255
WHILE WE TRANSPORT YOU
AND YOUR CARGO TO THE VESSEL.

20:13.342 --> 20:15.170
STEP FOUR, MR. RYAN FILES
FAUX ROUTING PAPERS.

20:15.257 --> 20:16.867
IF ANYONE COMES
LOOKING FOR YOU,

20:16.954 --> 20:18.826
THEY'LL START THEIR SEARCH
IN CALAIS, FRANCE,

20:18.913 --> 20:21.307
4,000 MILES FROM
YOUR ACTUAL LOCATION.

20:21.394 --> 20:24.571
NOT BAD.
BUT YOU SKIPPED STEP THREE.

20:24.658 --> 20:26.616
STEP THREE IS THE REASON
YOU HIRED ME.

20:26.703 --> 20:29.184
HANDLE YOUR END.
TRUST ME TO HANDLE MINE.

20:31.534 --> 20:33.014
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:35.451 --> 20:37.888
CAFFREY'S PRETTY SAVVY
AT PLANNING AN ESCAPE.

20:37.975 --> 20:40.195
YEAH. UNTIL LAWRENCE
MAKES HIS MOVE,

20:40.282 --> 20:43.459
HE KNOWS WE'LL KEEP
HIS ANKLET OFF.

20:43.546 --> 20:45.287
ARE YOU GONNA LETHIM
WALK AROUND UNMONITORED?

20:45.374 --> 20:47.246
NO.

20:50.901 --> 20:53.295
YOU ARE TO CHECK IN
EVERY TWO HOURS ON THE HOUR.

20:53.382 --> 20:55.645
YOU GO FROM HOME TO THE OFFICE,
AND THAT'S IT.

20:55.732 --> 20:56.994
I KNOW THE DRILL.

20:57.081 --> 20:59.127
YOU'RE NOT OFF ANKLET
FOR GOOD BEHAVIOR.

20:59.214 --> 21:01.216
AFTER LAWRENCE GETS YOU
TO HIS MONEY,

21:01.303 --> 21:02.565
TAKE HIM TO THE HARBOR.

21:02.652 --> 21:04.132
WE'VE BEEN OVER THIS.
ANYTHING ELSE?

21:04.219 --> 21:06.613
YEAH.
WHAT'S STEP THREE?

21:06.700 --> 21:08.397
STEP THREE
IS YOU ARREST HIM.

21:08.484 --> 21:10.486
OH. GOOD THING
YOU DIDN'T TELL HIM.

21:10.573 --> 21:11.748
I THOUGHT
YOU MIGHT LIKE THAT.

21:11.835 --> 21:14.360
HMM.

21:14.447 --> 21:17.058
HEARD YOU TALKED TO EL.

21:17.145 --> 21:19.452
LOOK, PETER, WHATEVER
YOU THINK I HAVE DONE,

21:19.539 --> 21:21.410
YOU AND ME -- HEY.

21:21.497 --> 21:23.238
WE'RE ON THE SAME TEAM.

21:23.325 --> 21:25.196
REALLY?
YES.

21:25.284 --> 21:27.155
[ CELL PHONE RINGS ]MAY I?

21:27.242 --> 21:28.722
YES. GET OUT!THANK YOU.

21:28.809 --> 21:30.898
TALK TO YOU
IN TWO HOURS.

21:30.985 --> 21:32.943
AND TWO HOURS AFTER THAT.Peter:
THAT'S WHAT I LIKE TO HEAR.

21:33.030 --> 21:34.684
HEY, MOZ.

21:34.771 --> 21:36.904
OUR HUNCH MAY BE CORRECT.

21:36.991 --> 21:40.342
MRS. SUIT IS CHATTING UP HER OLD
BOSS AT THE DeARMITT GALLERY.

21:40.429 --> 21:41.474
WHAT'D SHE SAY?

21:41.561 --> 21:43.389
[ GROANS ]

21:43.476 --> 21:45.260
"Oh, what a spring
we're having."

21:45.347 --> 21:46.566
Blah blah blah.

21:46.653 --> 21:48.959
OH, SHE'S ASKING HIM
ABOUT A LAB TEST.

21:49.046 --> 21:52.659
OH! S-SHE'S GIVING HIM
A SCRAP OF BURNT PAINTING.

21:52.746 --> 21:53.573
IS IT MINE?

21:55.488 --> 21:58.099
OH, SWEET ELVIS COSTELLO!
IT'S YOUR CHRYSLER PAINTING!

22:00.101 --> 22:01.885
IT DIDN'T BURN.

22:01.972 --> 22:04.584
FLAME IS A FICKLE MISTRESS.

22:04.671 --> 22:06.150
WE'RE GONNA
HAVE TO STEAL IT.

22:06.237 --> 22:07.630
NO.
NO, NO, NO, NO.

22:07.717 --> 22:10.154
PETER WILL SUSPECT ME.

22:10.241 --> 22:12.940
LET THEM RUN THE TESTS.
WE'LL SWAP IT OUT.

22:14.855 --> 22:17.292
RISKY
BUT NOT IMPOSSIBLE.

22:17.379 --> 22:21.470
We need a swatch of canvas
and some paints from the 1930s.

22:21.557 --> 22:23.951
WHICH WE HAVE
IN GREAT SUPPLY.

22:24.038 --> 22:26.606
ALL RIGHT. MEET ME AT
THE WAREHOUSE. I'M ON MY WAY.

22:48.976 --> 22:51.108
[ CELL PHONE RINGS ]

22:51.195 --> 22:53.241
WHERE ARE YOU?

22:53.328 --> 22:54.895
Neal: I'VE GOT A TAIL.What?!

22:54.982 --> 22:55.983
HAVE YOU STARTED?

22:56.070 --> 22:58.072
OF COURSE I STARTED,

22:58.159 --> 23:00.901
BUT WITHOUT YOU HERE, I'M NOT
SURE WHICH COLORS TO SAMPLE,

23:00.988 --> 23:03.382
SO THIS WHOLE THING MIGHT BE
AN EXERCISE IN FUTILITY.

23:03.469 --> 23:05.775
JUST PULL THE PRIMARIES.
I CAN MIX THE REST.

23:05.862 --> 23:07.168
I'M NOT AN IDIOT.

23:07.255 --> 23:09.953
I SCRAPED A TITANIUM WHITE
FROM THE REMBRANDT,

23:10.040 --> 23:11.694
A MIDNIGHT BLUE
FROM A VLAMINCK.

23:11.781 --> 23:13.479
OH, YOU SHOULD GET
A MONESTIAL BLUE.

23:13.566 --> 23:15.959
YOU KNOW, I SHOULDGET
A MONESTIAL BLUE.

23:16.046 --> 23:18.832
IF YOU FIND ONE THICK ENOUGH,
FEEL FREE TO LET ME KNOW.

23:18.919 --> 23:20.616
OH, THAT'S RIGHT --
YOU'RE NOT HERE!

23:20.703 --> 23:22.575
Breathe, Moz.

23:22.662 --> 23:24.403
HOW ARE WE DOING ON THE CANVAS?
DID YOU CHECK THE DALí?

23:24.490 --> 23:25.839
EVIDENTLY...

23:25.926 --> 23:29.756
OUR FRIEND SALVADOR
LIKED TO STRETCH TIME

23:29.843 --> 23:31.453
BUT NOT CANVASES.

23:31.540 --> 23:34.021
I'LL FIND SOMETHING.

23:34.108 --> 23:36.197
I KNOW YOU WILL.

23:48.339 --> 23:50.080
PRACTICING?

23:50.167 --> 23:52.213
YEAH, I FIGURED I SHOULD
HAVE A COPY OF THE
CHRYSLER LYING AROUND

23:52.300 --> 23:53.867
IN CASE PETER CAME
LOOKING FOR IT.

23:53.954 --> 23:55.216
YOU GET EVERYTHING?

23:55.303 --> 23:57.914
SOME CANVAS AND A SPECTRUM
OF PREWAR PAINT

23:58.001 --> 24:00.482
THAT WOULD PASS ANY WOOD'S LIGHT
OR I.R. SPECTROSCOPY

24:00.569 --> 24:02.136
THEY WANT TO THROW AT IT.

24:02.223 --> 24:06.140
THE RED IS FROM A PORTRAIT
OF FERNANDE OLIVIER.

24:06.227 --> 24:08.534
THE LAST PERSON TO MIX
THIS PAINT WAS PICASSO.

24:08.621 --> 24:10.797
[ CHUCKLES ]WE'RE TAKING FROM MASTERS.

24:10.884 --> 24:13.495
OH, PICASSO WAS A COMMUNIST.
HE'D BE HAPPY TO SHARE.

24:13.582 --> 24:14.670
WHAT'S THE PLAN
FOR THE GALLERY?

24:14.757 --> 24:17.717
AH!
THE PLAN FOR THE GALLERY.

24:17.804 --> 24:21.198
I PRIED SOME INFORMATION
FROM A LOOSE-LIPPED GALLERISTA.

24:21.285 --> 24:23.505
THEY'RE SENDING OUR SWATCH OUT
TO AN AUTHENTICATION LAB

24:23.592 --> 24:25.202
AT 11:00 A.M.
TOMORROW MORNING.

24:25.289 --> 24:26.900
THE GALLERY OPENS AT 10:30,

24:26.987 --> 24:29.032
SO WE HAVE 30 MINUTES
TO GET INSIDE,

24:29.119 --> 24:30.686
MAKE THE SWITCH,
THEN GET OUT.

24:30.773 --> 24:32.427
IT'S GONNA BE CLOSE.
SECURITY?

24:32.514 --> 24:36.083
A STANDARD SCHLAGEL ON THE DOOR,
WITH SURVEILLANCE CAMERAS.

24:36.170 --> 24:38.477
WE'LL NEED A DISTRACTION
WHILE I PICK IT.

24:38.564 --> 24:41.349
I CAN'T BUY YOU THAT MUCH TIME
BY MYSELF.

24:41.436 --> 24:43.264
HOW ABOUT A KANSAS CITY
MUD SLIDE?

24:43.351 --> 24:44.570
YOU GONNA WORK
THE JACKHAMMER?

24:44.657 --> 24:47.703
NO.

24:47.790 --> 24:51.185
[ SNAPS FINGERS ]
LET'S RUN A PHOEBE CATES.WHO'S THE GIRL?

24:51.272 --> 24:53.535
I DON'T THINK JUNE WOULD MIND
IF WE USED HER GRANDDAUGHTER.

24:53.622 --> 24:54.754
WELL, SHE'S PRETTY ENOUGH.

24:54.841 --> 24:56.190
WILL SHE DO IT
WITHOUT ASKING QUESTIONS?

24:56.277 --> 24:57.496
I'M SURE SHE'S UP
FOR A LITTLE EXCITEMENT.

24:57.583 --> 24:58.758
EXCELLENT!

24:58.845 --> 25:00.629
OH -- NOW ON
TO THE BIGGER QUESTION.

25:00.716 --> 25:02.326
HOW DO YOU PLAN
ON LOSING YOUR TAIL,

25:02.413 --> 25:03.502
OUTSIDE EVOLUTION?

25:08.158 --> 25:10.770
I'LL TAKE A PAGE
FROM MAGRITTE.

25:19.518 --> 25:21.824
AH, YOU GOT TO BE KIDDING ME.

25:27.438 --> 25:28.483
CAFFREY!

25:30.964 --> 25:32.618
DID I WIN?

25:32.705 --> 25:34.968
THE CONTEST --
"WEAR A DARK SUIT, FEDORA,

25:35.055 --> 25:36.230
"COME TO 23rd AND 10th.

25:36.317 --> 25:38.232
BEST-DRESSED
WINS 500 BUCKS."

25:38.319 --> 25:39.450
YEAH. YEAH.

25:39.538 --> 25:41.148
YOU WON!

25:42.366 --> 25:45.544
OKAY, MOZ. YOU'RE UP.

25:48.416 --> 25:51.245
HEY, I HAVE A DELIVERY
FOR A THOMAS JOHNSON.

25:51.332 --> 25:53.552
YOU JUST MISSED HIM.
TOM TOOK A JOB IN BOSTON.

25:53.639 --> 25:55.031
HIS LAST DAY WAS MONDAY.

25:55.118 --> 25:56.772
OH, DAMN.
CAN'T BLAME HIM, THOUGH.

25:56.859 --> 25:59.514
BOSTON'S A HELL OF A TOWN.

26:01.821 --> 26:03.431
SOMETHING
I CAN HELP YOU WITH?

26:03.518 --> 26:05.172
NO, I'M JUST
ADMIRING THE VIEW.

26:07.000 --> 26:08.349
NICE, HUH?

26:09.611 --> 26:12.353
OH.YEAH.

26:14.964 --> 26:16.662
LOOK WHAT I DID.
I GOT IT ALL OVER ME.

26:16.749 --> 26:17.576
UGH.

26:25.540 --> 26:27.716
THERE IS SOMETHING
VERY SERIOUSLY WRONG WITH ME.

26:27.803 --> 26:29.500
TODAY OF ALL DAYS.
WOULD YOU MIND HOLDING THIS?

26:29.588 --> 26:31.415
Mozzie: OH. UH, SURE.AND COULD YOU TAKE THIS?

26:31.502 --> 26:33.069
O-OKAY, BUT --

26:33.156 --> 26:34.897
AND I'M GONNA NEED YOU
TO HOLD THIS UP FOR ME.

26:34.984 --> 26:36.464
UH-HUH.

26:36.551 --> 26:38.074
OH. OF COURSE.

26:38.161 --> 26:39.728
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA! MISS! YOU
CAN'T TAKE YOUR TOP OFF HERE.

26:39.815 --> 26:41.643
LOOK, I DON'T THINK
YOU GET IT.

26:41.730 --> 26:43.340
I CAN'T BE LATE TODAY,
OKAY?

26:43.427 --> 26:44.820
MY BOSS WILL KILL ME
IF I'M LATE.

26:44.907 --> 26:48.868
C-COME ON, MAN.
LET HER CHANGE!

26:48.955 --> 26:50.434
YEAH.
I GUESS IT COULDN'T HURT.

26:50.521 --> 26:52.262
UH, JUST BE QUICK
ABOUT IT, OKAY?

26:52.349 --> 26:54.700
THANKS, GUYS, REALLY.

26:54.787 --> 26:56.658
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT THIS MEANS TO ME.

26:56.745 --> 26:59.182
OH, OR...US.

27:00.793 --> 27:02.185
WHICH TOP DO YOU LIKE?

27:03.970 --> 27:05.014
THIS OR THIS?

27:05.101 --> 27:07.495
Guard:
UH, TH-THE SECOND ONE.

27:07.582 --> 27:10.019
YOU GUYS ARE WONDERFUL.

27:10.106 --> 27:12.543
YEAH, JUST A COUPLE
OF WORKING STIFFS

27:12.631 --> 27:15.024
DOING WHAT WE CAN TO HELP OUT
A LADY IN DISTRESS.

27:15.111 --> 27:16.373
[ CHUCKLES ]

27:16.460 --> 27:18.462
ALMOST THERE.

27:21.422 --> 27:23.729
PERFECT.
WE ARE GOOD TO GO.

27:35.523 --> 27:37.264
GREAT.

27:41.050 --> 27:42.617
YOU ARE A LIFESAVER.

27:44.532 --> 27:46.229
YOU TOO.

27:46.316 --> 27:48.275
[ SMOOCHES ]

27:53.759 --> 27:55.151
SCREW BOSTON.

27:55.238 --> 27:56.805
THISIS A HELL OF A TOWN.

28:17.086 --> 28:18.305
YEAH.

28:51.512 --> 28:54.384
[ CELL PHONE VIBRATES ]

28:54.471 --> 28:56.865
HEY, PETER.

28:56.952 --> 28:59.563
YOU GAVE JONES
A NICE RUNAROUND.

28:59.650 --> 29:02.175
THAT WAS JONES? I THOUGHT
THAT COULD'VE BEEN LAWRENCE.

29:02.262 --> 29:03.219
I DIDN'T WANT
TO BLOW MY COVER.

29:03.306 --> 29:04.438
MM-HMM.

29:04.525 --> 29:06.005
WHY'D YOU PUT JONES ON ME?

29:06.092 --> 29:08.703
YOU REALLY WANT ME TO
ANSWER THAT? YOU AT HOME?

29:08.790 --> 29:10.139
WHERE ELSE WOULD I BE?

29:10.226 --> 29:11.445
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

29:11.532 --> 29:13.969
YOU KNOW, ARTS AND CRAFTS --
THE USUAL.

29:14.056 --> 29:16.102
JONES WILL BE AT YOUR PLACE
IN 20 MINUTES.

29:16.189 --> 29:18.452
HE'S GONNA STAY ON YOU.
YOU'RE GONNA LET HIM.

29:18.539 --> 29:20.193
NO PROBLEM.
Bye.

29:31.552 --> 29:33.249
[ CHUCKLES ]

29:39.865 --> 29:42.432
SO, I'M GETTING EVERYTHING
IN PLACE AT THE WAREHOUSE.

29:42.519 --> 29:45.044
THE PLANE
IS FUELED AND READY.

29:45.131 --> 29:47.046
YOU KNOW JONES
IS OUTSIDE, RIGHT?

29:47.133 --> 29:48.787
YEAH. ONCE I GET LAWRENCE
AND HIS MONEY TO THE DOCKS,

29:48.874 --> 29:50.179
I CAN SLIP HIM AGAIN.

29:50.266 --> 29:51.572
[ CHUCKLES ]

29:51.659 --> 29:53.792
BY THE TIME LAWRENCE
IS BEING HAULED DOWNTOWN,

29:53.879 --> 29:56.229
WE'LL BE SIPPING CHAMPAGNE
AT CRUISING ALTITUDE.

29:56.316 --> 29:57.621
SO, WHEN'S "GO" TIME?

29:59.798 --> 30:01.800
LAWRENCE'S TEXT CAME IN
TWO MINUTES AGO.

30:03.149 --> 30:04.411
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME?

30:04.498 --> 30:05.760
THIS IS IT!

30:05.847 --> 30:08.632
WE TAKE OUR TIME.
WE DO IT RIGHT.

30:08.719 --> 30:10.460
LOOK, YOU KNOW,

30:10.547 --> 30:14.247
EVERYTHING GOOD MUST ONE DAY
COME TO AN END.

30:14.334 --> 30:15.988
JUST THINK --

30:16.075 --> 30:18.425
WE'RE NEVER GONNA SEE ANYTHING
IN THIS APARTMENT AGAIN --

30:18.512 --> 30:22.124
EXCEPT YOU.
YOU CAN COME WITH ME.

30:22.211 --> 30:24.648
Mozzie: HEY.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

30:24.735 --> 30:26.520
THIS IS OUR
FINAL CURTAIN CALL,

30:26.607 --> 30:28.043
OUR BIG AU REVOIR.

30:28.130 --> 30:29.871
I SHOULD SAY SOMETHING
TO JUNE.

30:29.958 --> 30:34.397
HEY. YOU KNOW THE RULES.
NO GOOD-BYES.

30:34.484 --> 30:35.529
YEAH.

30:37.052 --> 30:38.314
I'M GONNA MISS HER, TOO.

30:38.401 --> 30:40.316
I'M...

30:41.883 --> 30:43.276
...GONNA MISS ALL OF IT.

30:45.234 --> 30:46.366
COME ON.

30:46.453 --> 30:47.628
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

30:47.715 --> 30:49.804
I'LL SEE YOU DOWNSTAIRS.OKAY.

31:06.603 --> 31:09.563
[ SCOFFS ]

31:17.963 --> 31:19.878
GOOD-BYE, CAFFREY.

31:33.282 --> 31:34.849
LAWRENCE MADE CONTACT?

31:34.936 --> 31:36.024
I'M ON MY WAY
TO THE FENCING CLUB

31:36.111 --> 31:37.156
TO MEET HIM NOW.

31:37.243 --> 31:38.766
UPDATE ME
WHEN YOU HAVE THE MONEY.

31:38.853 --> 31:40.724
JONES WILL BACK YOUR PLAY
IF ANYTHING GOES WRONG.

31:40.811 --> 31:42.161
I'M HEADING
TO THE HARBOR NOW.

31:42.248 --> 31:44.032
ALL RIGHT.

31:53.520 --> 31:55.652
EVERYTHING IN PLACE?

31:55.739 --> 31:58.046
MM.

31:58.133 --> 31:59.743
ONLY THING LEFT
IS THE MONEY.

31:59.830 --> 32:01.267
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:01.354 --> 32:04.966
THE FEDERAL RESERVE JOB --
IT WAS FLAWLESS.

32:05.053 --> 32:06.925
PROBABLY THE MOST SECURE VAULT
IN THE WORLD,

32:07.012 --> 32:08.796
AND I WALKED OUT
WITH $60 MILLION.

32:08.883 --> 32:10.580
IT WAS PROMETHEUS...

32:10.667 --> 32:13.975
STEALING FIRE
FROM THE GODS.

32:14.062 --> 32:15.846
PROMETHEUS GOT CAUGHT.[ CHUCKLES ]

32:15.934 --> 32:17.326
YES, HE DID.

32:17.413 --> 32:19.502
YES, HE DID.

32:19.589 --> 32:21.591
AND THE FBI CLOSED IN --
FAST.

32:21.678 --> 32:23.332
EVERY ACCOUNT, P.O. BOX,
STORAGE LOCKER,

32:23.419 --> 32:24.812
FRIENDS, RELATIVES,
APARTMENTS.

32:24.899 --> 32:26.640
THEY WERE ALL OVER ME.

32:26.727 --> 32:30.122
I NEEDED TO GET OUT FAST,
STASH THE MONEY.

32:30.209 --> 32:31.601
I THOUGHT I'D BE BACK
IN 48 HOURS TO COLLECT IT,

32:31.688 --> 32:35.170
BUT THE FEDS WERE THERE,
WAITING.

32:35.257 --> 32:37.912
INSTEAD, I WAS ON A PLANE
HEADED SOUTH OF THE BORDER.

32:37.999 --> 32:39.522
EVERY MORNING,
I'D CHECK THE NEWS,

32:39.609 --> 32:41.437
WAITING TO HEAR
THE REPORT --

32:41.524 --> 32:44.658
"$60 MILLION FOUND
IN GRAMERCY FENCING CLUB."

32:44.745 --> 32:46.355
IT'S HERE?

32:46.442 --> 32:48.836
THERE ARE FIVE DUCTS
TO THIS ROOM.

32:48.923 --> 32:51.143
I DIVERTED AIR
TO TWO OF THEM.

32:51.230 --> 32:52.448
[ CLICK ]

32:52.535 --> 32:55.321
[ AIR RUSHING, DUCTS CLANGING ]

33:01.849 --> 33:03.459
THERE IT IS --

33:03.546 --> 33:05.940
$60 MILLION.

33:06.027 --> 33:09.639
YOU KNOW HOW MANY TIMES
I PICTURED THIS IN MY HEAD?

33:09.726 --> 33:11.641
IS THIS HOW YOU THOUGHT
IT'D FEEL?

33:11.728 --> 33:13.339
NO.

33:13.426 --> 33:15.254
BETTER.

33:15.341 --> 33:18.300
[ LAUGHS ]

33:25.786 --> 33:28.093
WHAT'S GOING ON?

33:31.270 --> 33:33.620
SOMEONE KNOWS WE'RE HERE.

33:43.108 --> 33:44.413
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

33:44.500 --> 33:45.501
AGENT JONES.

33:47.503 --> 33:49.244
FBI.

33:49.331 --> 33:50.550
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

33:50.637 --> 33:52.117
[ GUN COCKS ]

33:52.204 --> 33:53.466
TALK, OR I SHOOT.

33:53.553 --> 33:54.728
YOU TAILING
MY FRIEND HERE?

33:54.815 --> 33:56.686
ANSWER HIM.

33:56.773 --> 33:58.601
WERE YOU FOLLOWING ME?

33:58.688 --> 34:01.082
I DON'T KNOW WHO YOU ARE.

34:01.169 --> 34:03.215
I'M ON LAWRENCE.

34:03.302 --> 34:05.130
HOW MANY OF YOUR FRIENDS
YOU GOT OUT THERE?

34:05.217 --> 34:06.740
I FOLLOWED A HUNCH.

34:06.827 --> 34:08.176
I'M BY MYSELF.

34:08.263 --> 34:10.004
LIAR!

34:10.091 --> 34:11.658
A PACK OF WOLVES!

34:14.313 --> 34:16.924
THEY PROBABLY KNOW
ABOUT THE DOCK.

34:17.011 --> 34:19.144
THE WHOLE THING IS BLOWN.

34:19.231 --> 34:22.234
KILL HIM.
DUMP THE BODY.

34:22.321 --> 34:24.149
W-W-WAIT A SECOND.

34:24.236 --> 34:26.455
THIS GUY
IS USELESS DEAD.

34:26.542 --> 34:28.066
ALIVE, HE'S LEVERAGE.

34:28.153 --> 34:29.241
FOR WHAT?

34:29.328 --> 34:31.156
YOU FORGOT STEP THREE.

34:31.243 --> 34:33.462
ATTAQUE COMPOSéE --
FEINT LEFT, THRUST RIGHT.

34:33.549 --> 34:34.898
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

34:34.985 --> 34:37.249
I'M TALKING ABOUT
A BACKUP PLAN.

34:37.336 --> 34:39.729
WHEN IT ALL GOES TO HELL,
THIS IS WHY YOU HIRE ME.

34:41.035 --> 34:43.342
I'VE GOT A PLANE.

34:48.869 --> 34:51.045
[ CELL PHONE RINGS ]

34:52.612 --> 34:54.570
NOW BOARDING --

34:54.657 --> 34:57.443
Freedom Airlines,
flight number one and only.

34:57.530 --> 34:58.922
I'M HERE WITH THE CLIENT.

34:59.009 --> 35:00.794
WE'RE PUTTING STEP THREE
INTO EFFECT.

35:00.881 --> 35:03.318
STEP THREE? NEAL, WHAT
ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

35:03.405 --> 35:05.407
THE CLIENT AND I ARE MOVING
THE CARGO TO THE AIRSTRIP.

35:05.494 --> 35:06.930
Client?

35:07.017 --> 35:08.671
DON'T TELL ME YOU'RE
TALKING ABOUT LAWRENCE.

35:08.758 --> 35:10.499
THAT'S RIGHT.No. No, no, no.

35:10.586 --> 35:11.979
DON'T DO THIS TO US.

35:12.066 --> 35:15.983
MAKE SURE IT'S GASSED UP
AND GOOD TO GO. ALL RIGHT?

35:16.070 --> 35:18.028
GRAB YOUR SUIT
AND MEET ME THERE.

35:18.116 --> 35:21.249
WHAT? NO SUITS.
NO SUITS ON THE ISLAND!

35:22.816 --> 35:24.687
NEAL --

35:27.255 --> 35:28.778
NO SIGN OF CAFFREY
AND LAWRENCE.

35:28.865 --> 35:30.389
STILL NO ANSWER
FROM JONES.

35:30.476 --> 35:32.086
THIS IS TAKING
WAY TOO LONG.

35:32.173 --> 35:34.610
[ CELL PHONE RINGS ]

35:34.697 --> 35:36.830
YOU BETTER HAVE A GOOD REASON
FOR CALLING.

35:36.917 --> 35:38.919
I'm in the middle of something
very important, Mozzie.

35:39.006 --> 35:41.443
YEAH,
YOU AND ME BOTH, SUIT.

35:41.530 --> 35:43.793
I'M PASSING ON A MESSAGE
FROM NEAL.

35:43.880 --> 35:45.839
HE'S MADE A REQUEST
FOR OUR PRESENCE,

35:45.926 --> 35:47.406
WITHOUT THE SLIGHTEST REGARD

35:47.493 --> 35:50.191
FOR THE MONUMENTAL INCONVENIENCE
IT CAUSES US --

35:50.278 --> 35:51.888
PRIMARILY, ME.

35:51.975 --> 35:54.369
Van Buren airstrip.
30 minutes.

35:54.456 --> 35:56.154
MOVING OUT.

36:03.639 --> 36:06.773
NEAL, WE GOT TO HURRY.

36:08.166 --> 36:10.037
I SAID, "SUIT,"
NOT "COSTUME."

36:10.124 --> 36:12.779
DON'T WORRY.
THE SUIT GOT THE MESSAGE.

36:14.998 --> 36:16.174
Lawrence:
LOAD THE FED UP FRONT.

36:19.089 --> 36:20.787
JONES?

36:20.874 --> 36:21.744
WHY AREN'T WE FLYING?

36:26.445 --> 36:28.098
YOU SURE
YOU CAN FLY THIS THING?

36:37.282 --> 36:39.545
[ ENGINES WHIRRING ]

36:42.025 --> 36:44.289
[ TIRES SCREECH,
SIRENS WAILING ]

36:46.247 --> 36:47.944
GET AROUND THE FRONT
OF THAT PLANE.

36:48.031 --> 36:49.381
TEAM ONE, FLANK LEFT.

36:49.468 --> 36:51.296
TEAM THREE, FLANK RIGHT.
BOX HIM IN!

36:51.383 --> 36:54.429
WE CANNOT LET CAFFREY
GET AIRBORNE!

36:54.516 --> 36:57.954
LOLANA, IT WASN'T SUPPOSED TO
BE LIKE THIS.

36:58.041 --> 36:59.521
[ WAILING CONTINUES ]

36:59.608 --> 37:00.348
GET US OUT OF HERE.

37:02.089 --> 37:03.264
WE'RE NOT GONNA MAKE IT.

37:03.351 --> 37:05.484
WE DON'T HAVE A CHOICE,
MOZ.

37:07.660 --> 37:10.184
WE HAVETO MAKE IT.

37:16.364 --> 37:18.758
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

37:18.845 --> 37:21.108
Lawrence: CLIMB.

37:21.195 --> 37:22.936
Mozzie:
WE NEED MORE SPEED.

37:23.023 --> 37:25.025
Lawrence: CLIMB NOW!

37:32.250 --> 37:34.252
WATCH OUT![ TIRES SCREECH ]

37:39.082 --> 37:41.607
[ WAILING CONTINUES ]

37:41.694 --> 37:43.086
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

37:43.173 --> 37:44.740
Man: FBI!

37:44.827 --> 37:46.699
COME OUT NOW
WITH YOUR HANDS UP!

37:48.178 --> 37:49.528
LET ME SEE YOUR HANDS!Jones: WE'RE SECURE!

37:49.615 --> 37:52.574
LAWRENCE IS ON THE PLANE!

37:58.188 --> 38:00.321
Diana: YOU OKAY?I'M GOOD.

38:00.408 --> 38:02.584
Peter:
YOU ALL RIGHT, JONES?
YEAH.

38:02.671 --> 38:04.064
CAFFREY HAD MY BACK.

38:04.151 --> 38:06.719
YOUR TIMING IS FAR
FROM IMPECCABLE, J. EDGAR.

38:06.806 --> 38:08.764
SORRY...AMELIA.

38:08.851 --> 38:12.028
LUCKILY, I WAS HERE
TO SAVE THE DAY ONCE AGAIN.

38:12.115 --> 38:14.292
YOU'RE A HERO, MOZ.
I'LL SEW YOU A CAPE.

38:14.379 --> 38:16.946
DO THAT.
I LOOK GOOD IN AUBERGINE.

38:17.033 --> 38:19.253
THANK YOU.

38:24.258 --> 38:26.173
STEP THREE, HUH?

38:26.260 --> 38:27.653
THE PART
WHERE YOU ARREST HIM.

38:27.740 --> 38:28.784
NICE WORK.

38:28.871 --> 38:30.743
THANKS.

38:32.745 --> 38:35.095
AH, THE ANKLET.

38:45.323 --> 38:46.498
HEY, HON.

38:46.585 --> 38:48.195
HEY. GOOD DAY?

38:48.282 --> 38:50.415
UH, WE CAUGHT A BAD GUY,
SO IT WASN'T A BAD DAY.

38:50.502 --> 38:52.155
HMM. WELL.
MWAH!

38:52.242 --> 38:53.809
THISSHOULD MAKE YOU FEEL
EVEN BETTER.

38:53.896 --> 38:58.336
AUTHENTICATION FROM THE GALLERY.
THE CANVAS IS MID-1930s.

38:58.423 --> 39:00.381
SO, IT WASN'T
NEAL'S PAINTING.

39:00.468 --> 39:03.776
WELL, UNLESS HE PAINTED IT
75 YEARS AGO.

39:06.256 --> 39:08.563
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

39:46.427 --> 39:47.472
HI, PETER.

39:52.694 --> 39:53.782
I LET MYSELF IN.

39:53.869 --> 39:56.524
YEAH. YEAH, YOU DID.

39:57.960 --> 40:01.355
JUST CLEARING OUT SOME SPACE
FOR STORAGE.

40:02.835 --> 40:04.053
YOU LIKE THAT ONE?

40:05.925 --> 40:07.274
YEAH.

40:07.361 --> 40:08.667
YOU CAN HAVE IT.

40:10.320 --> 40:12.540
I'VE ALREADY GOT THE VIEW.

40:12.627 --> 40:14.499
MM-HMM.

40:18.807 --> 40:21.375
[ SIGHS ] WHEW.

40:24.813 --> 40:25.988
I'M CALLING A TRUCE.

40:27.555 --> 40:30.210
I MAY HAVE RUSHED
TO JUDGMENT.

40:30.297 --> 40:33.518
OH, YOU HAD JUDGMENT
ON SPEED DIAL.

40:33.605 --> 40:35.215
I'M TRYING
TO BE GRACIOUS.

40:35.302 --> 40:37.696
YOU KEPT MY SEVERED TIE.

40:38.958 --> 40:40.568
I WAS PRETTY PISSED OFF.

40:40.655 --> 40:41.743
AND NOW?

40:41.830 --> 40:43.789
LOOK AT THIS.

40:43.876 --> 40:45.443
I'M SMILING AGAIN.

40:45.530 --> 40:47.488
[ CHUCKLES ] I LIKE IT.

40:47.575 --> 40:48.794
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

40:48.881 --> 40:50.230
[ CELL PHONE RINGS ]

40:56.845 --> 40:58.020
I GOT TO GO.

40:58.107 --> 40:59.457
OKAY.

41:02.938 --> 41:05.071
PETER...
HMM?

41:05.158 --> 41:07.073
DOOR'S OPEN ANYTIME.

41:07.160 --> 41:09.467
THANKS.

41:11.773 --> 41:13.514
WHAT DO YOU HAVE?

41:13.601 --> 41:15.168
E.R.T.'s STILL DOING
A CLEANUP OF THE WAREHOUSE

41:15.255 --> 41:16.648
AND THE U-BOAT BURN.

41:16.735 --> 41:18.476
THEY FOUND THIS
ABOUT AN HOUR AGO.

41:18.563 --> 41:19.781
WHAT IS IT?

41:19.868 --> 41:22.175
PART OF THE ORIGINAL
GERMAN U-BOAT MANIFEST.

41:22.262 --> 41:25.178
WE CAN MAKE OUT 22 OF THE
PAINTINGS THAT WERE ON BOARD.

41:25.265 --> 41:27.180
WHO ELSE KNOWS ABOUT THIS?

41:27.267 --> 41:28.834
UH, TWO PEOPLE ON
THE EVIDENCE RECOVERY TEAM,

41:28.921 --> 41:30.009
JONES, AND ME.

41:30.096 --> 41:31.706
KEEP IT THAT WAY.

41:33.447 --> 41:35.797
WE HAVE TO SELL SOMETHING.

41:35.884 --> 41:37.886
WHY?

41:37.973 --> 41:40.498
WELL, OUR FIRST ESCAPE
WAS COMPROMISED.

41:40.585 --> 41:43.152
WE HAVE TO FUND
THE SECOND.

41:43.239 --> 41:45.285
YOU STILL THINK
CAFFREY HAS THE ART?

41:45.372 --> 41:46.721
I DON'T KNOW.

41:46.808 --> 41:49.202
HE DID HAVE THAT GETAWAY
PLANE READY AWFULLY FAST.

41:49.289 --> 41:51.683
YEAH. YEAH. BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?
THAT DOESN'T MATTER.

41:51.770 --> 41:54.555
PATIENCE IS OUR BEST ASSET
RIGHT NOW.

41:54.642 --> 41:57.253
WHOEVER STOLE IT,
IF A SINGLE ITEM ON THIS LIST

41:57.340 --> 41:58.951
SHOWS UP ANYWHERE --WE GOT 'EM.

42:00.169 --> 42:02.520
YEAH. WE GOT 'EM.

42:04.043 --> 42:06.349
SIMPLE QUESTION --

42:06.436 --> 42:08.308
WHAT DO WE SELL FIRST?
